'''Tembora''' was a [[rogue moon]] in deep space near [[Geric IV]]. It was 1,200km in diameter with 0.15 standard gravity and practically no atmosphere, which meant that [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] vehicles were useless. It was the location of [[Tembora Research Station]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The station was attacked by [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] forces during the Clone Wars and the only ship guarding it, the ''[[Myrkos]]'', was badly damaged, plunging into Tembora&mdash;creating a two-kilometer-wide crater and causing Tembora's orbit to change. The [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] [[Army Weapons Research Department]] scientists at the station developed the [[KLR series combat droid]]s, but the prototype [[KLR-B1]] killed the scientists as well as whomever crashed on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]].

